✅🩸DIABETIC TIPS: “How to EAT Spike- Free at a Holiday Event!” 
🫒🍷🧀😀

Are you a Pre Diabetic or T2 Diabetic like me and you are concerned about your food choices at a holiday party??

I’m with you but I’m also PREPARED!!

✅ I took a couple of homemade keto wheat, low-carb yeast rolls to dinner and whipped them out when the breadbasket was past and I didn’t miss out one bit!😀

✅ If you are not a baker, you can always take a stash of nuts, dry cheeses, individual packaged olives, small celery sticks or enjoy them from the cheese board or appetizer selection!

✅If food choices are only heavy, high glycemic index carbs, take a very small portion and eat it VERY SLOWLY!!

✅Alternate bites of high carb foods with salad, nuts, cheese, or olives (good fats and proteins) or a nice, dry wine!!

✅FYI- Your body will digest the alcohol in the wine BEFORE it digests the carbs so if you alternate a sip of wine with carbs it will act like a “speed bump” helping to avoid a spike! 

✅Avoid sweet sugar-infused cocktails

Let’s be ready at all times to avoid blood sugar spikes! The damage from them is cumulative!

Let’s reverse that dumb Diabetes together and enjoy the holidays!

One week before Christmas is the best time to buy a living Christmas tree as they do best outdoors!!

✅Check the leaves and look for a tree with soft, supple leaves and say NO to trees with crispy dry leaves.

✅Check the roots to make sure they are not girdling and outgrowing the pot.

✅Place in a sunny location indoors although the Norfolk will tolerate less bright light.

✅Mist the Norfolk pine and add humidity as much as possible!

✅Water as often as needed to keep the soil from drying out. This tree needs moisture!

OMG! “”Low Carb, SUGAR-FREE EGGNOG”
✅Diabetic Friendly 🩸😍
✅ Keto / Low carb / Sugar Free Diets

Are you a Pre Diabetic or T2 DIABETIC like me and you miss Eggnog because all the sugar spikes your blood sugar??

✅MAKE MY SUGAR FREE EGGNIG!😍

Ingredients

2 cups Unsweetened Almond milk or other nut milk or low carb milk substitute 

2 cups Heavy Whipping Cream

2 cinnamon sticks

1/2 tsp (or more) grated Nutmeg

6 Egg Yolks

3/4 cup to 1 cup Allulose sugar substitute or other (monkfruit, erythritol, etc)

2 teaspoon Vanilla extract

*Optional 1/4 - 1 cup alcohol of choice

-Whisk or hand mixer

STEPS

1. Mix and warm up the 2 cups of milk substitute and 2 cups heavy cream with the 2 cinnamon sticks, nutmeg, and salt on low heat for about 8 minutes!

*Simmer till you see small bubbles in perimeter but don’t boil the milks!
Remove from fire and remove cinnamon sticks

Whisk or mix 6 egg yolks with 3/4 cup Allulose sugar substitute (more or less to taste) until eggs are light colored

*TEMPERING EGGS

Now that eggs are light and mixed well, SLOWLY add small amounts of the hot milk mix into the egg mixture while whisking to keep eggs from over-heating!

take your time so that you don’t curdle or “cook” your eggs! 

✅This is not scrambled eggs!

✅Once all the milk is incorporated into the eggs, return everything to the pot and return to stove on low heat!

🌹 Cut Flower Prep: ROSES 
❤️Just in time for VALENTINE'S DAY!❤️

There's no flower more suitable for cutting than the rose. Luckily, you do not have to work in a flower shop to put together the perfect rose arrangement!

▪️Choose roses with petals just starting to open. 
▪️Cut roses in the morning when they are the most hydrated.
▪️Cut the stems at an angle and close to the base of the rose bush. 
▪️Place cut flowers immediately into a bucket of water.
▪️When arranging for your vase, trim as much off the bottom as needed, cutting at a 45-degree angle while the stems are submerged in water. 
▪️Remove all of the leaves that would be underwater in the vase. This will prevent rot.

This particular coughing fit seemed more severe and foxy was panting and uncomfortable!

I took her to the animal hospital in the morning and they immediately put her in an oxygenated kennel, was given an IV for dehydration, and they treated her for an inflamed esophagus!

TIP: the vet asked us to raise her food and water bowls so that she doesn’t have to bend over to eat and drink and “kink” her esophagus!

🌿 Houseplant of the Day: POTHOS 

Elevate your indoor oasis with the timeless charm of Pothos! 

🏡 LOCATION: Pothos is a versatile plant that thrives in various locations. Whether hanging gracefully or placed on a shelf, it adds a touch of green to any space.
🌞 LIGHT: Pothos is adaptable to different light conditions. While it can tolerate low light, it thrives in bright, indirect light. 
💧 WATER: Allow the top inch of soil to dry before watering. Pothos is forgiving, so it's better to underwater than overwater. 
🌱 SOIL: Well-draining potting mix is ideal. Pothos isn't too picky about soil types.
🚫 TOXIC: Keep in mind that Pothos is toxic to pets and humans if ingested.
